pqueue = PQueue(batch_len=batch_len)
for method, item, batch in puts:
    getattr(pqueue, method)(item, batch)
ret = []
while not pqueue.empty():
    ret.append(pqueue.get())
assert ret == expect
pytest.mark.parametrize('batch_len,puts,expect', [(10, [('put', 5, 0), (
    'put', 0, 0), ('put', 7, 0), ('put_next', 4, 2), ('put_next', 6, 3), (
    'put_next', 3, 3), ('put', 3, 3), ('put', 6, 3)], [(0, 0), (3, 3), (6, 
    3), (4, 4), (3, 5), (5, 5), (6, 5), (7, 7)])])
